### Notes on inheritance / reporting

- **IU subtree inheritance (ADR 0004):** if the wrapper marks a command path as `intentionally_unsupported`, all descendant commands/flags/args are treated as IU and appear under `deltas.intentionally_unsupported` (not `missing_*`). Override by adding an exact wrapper coverage entry.
- **Global flags model:** some flags are treated as global (root) and are reported at `path=[]` to avoid per-command noise; fix root coverage for global flags. If you see the same flag reported missing under many subcommands, confirm whether it is truly global for that version by inspecting `snapshots/0.92.0/union.json`.
